                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Merry reports that arrangement of armistice for Wednesday—to-morrow
                    morning—is made and that the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> is expected to
                    arrive at San Jose de Guatemala from Acajutla Thursday morning to receive all
                    commissioners. Inquires whether he shall represent Costa Rica and Nicaragua, as
                    requested, Combs being absent, Brown to substitute.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
